OL,3,CEgg warning after cancer-causing
OL,4,Cchemicals found near plant
OL,6,FScientists took samples of eggs
OL,7,Fproduced by domestic poultry keepers
OL,8,Fwithin 1km of the site with results
OL,9,Fconfirming levels of a chemical, known
OL,10,Fto be a carcinogenic, was above the
OL,11,Frecommended weekly intake.
OL,13,FEating just one of these eggs per week
OL,14,Fcould go over the safe weekly limit,
OL,15,Fthe Food Standards Agency (FSA) said.
OL,17,FIt follows a similar warning, in 2025,
OL,18,Fwhere residents were told not to eat
OL,19,Ffruit and vegetables grown locally in
OL,20,Fthe soil due to the risk of
OL,21,Fcontamination.
